bring her to visit Archie.

1167
00:59:27,480 --> 00:59:29,030
And there's another thing.
- What?

1168
00:59:29,030 --> 00:59:31,503
- The kids said there was
something strange about her.

1169
00:59:32,350 --> 00:59:33,302
- What do you mean, strange?

1170
00:59:33,302 --> 00:59:35,052
I don't know. That's all they said.

1171
00:59:37,115 --> 00:59:39,782
(ominous tones)

1172
01:00:16,999 --> 01:00:19,666
(door rattling)

1173
01:00:39,352 --> 01:00:41,494
(door creaks)

1174
01:00:41,494 --> 01:00:42,327
Linda?

1175
01:00:42,327 --> 01:00:44,994
(ominous tones)

1176
01:00:49,943 --> 01:00:50,776
Linda?

1177
01:01:13,244 --> 01:01:14,077
Linda?

1178
01:01:18,056 --> 01:01:19,142
(electricity buzzes)

1179
01:01:19,142 --> 01:01:21,642
(Linda gasps)

1180
01:01:28,720 --> 01:01:30,050
- [Linda] Scared me to death.

1181
01:01:30,050 --> 01:01:30,883
- Me too.

1182
01:01:32,209 --> 01:01:33,160
- I just came into get a cup of coffee.

1183
01:01:33,160 --> 01:01:33,993
I'm doing books.

1184
01:01:33,993 --> 01:01:35,030
What are you doing here?

1185
01:01:35,030 --> 01:01:38,163
- Well, I think we should talk.

1186
01:01:40,417 --> 01:01:41,720
- [Linda] Would you like a cup of coffee?

1187
01:01:41,720 --> 01:01:43,073
- Oh, no thanks.

1188
01:01:51,680 --> 01:01:55,368
I'd like you and the kids
to come to LA for awhile.

1189
01:01:55,368 --> 01:01:58,440
- (scoffs) We can't do that.

1190
01:01:58,440 --> 01:01:59,273
I've got a job.

1191
01:01:59,273 --> 01:02:01,000
The kids are in school.

1192
01:02:01,000 --> 01:02:03,400
I can't-
- Just for a little while.

1193
01:02:03,400 --> 01:02:06,370
I mean, say you're taking a vacation.

1194
01:02:06,370 --> 01:02:08,560
Parents take their kids
outta school all the time.

1195
01:02:08,560 --> 01:02:09,560
They can make it up.

1196
01:02:11,667 --> 01:02:12,500
- And what about Eddie?

1197
01:02:12,500 --> 01:02:13,783
- This is not about Eddie.

1198
01:02:17,335 --> 01:02:19,330
(Linda sighs)

1199
01:02:19,330 --> 01:02:20,163
I'm sorry.

1200
01:02:21,470 --> 01:02:22,943
- What is this really about?

1201
01:02:26,120 --> 01:02:30,410
- It's about taking a break, you know,

1202
01:02:30,410 --> 01:02:31,660
from all that's happened.

1203
01:02:32,760 --> 01:02:35,810
Come on, you see the way Eddie's acting.

1204
01:02:35,810 --> 01:02:38,420
It's not good for you and
it's not good for the kids.

1205
01:02:38,420 --> 01:02:39,930
You know guys like Dad and Eddie,

1206
01:02:39,930 --> 01:02:42,460
well, they never think
of the consequences.

1207
01:02:42,460 --> 01:02:44,483
They're children and they're dangerous.

1208
01:02:47,330 --> 01:02:49,755
And they'll never grow up
because of people like...

1209
01:02:49,755 --> 01:02:52,255
(tense music)

1210
01:02:53,090 --> 01:02:53,923
Mother.

1211
01:02:57,131 --> 01:02:57,964
- And me.

1212
01:02:59,350 --> 01:03:02,463
Mother and me, that's
what you were gonna say.

1213
01:03:04,150 --> 01:03:05,190
You want us to leave town

1214
01:03:05,190 --> 01:03:07,500
'cause you're gonna testify against Eddie.

1215
01:03:07,500 --> 01:03:08,333
- Linda, honey.

1216
01:03:08,333 --> 01:03:12,090
Listen, it's time to think
about you and the kids.

1217
01:03:12,090 --> 01:03:14,510
- You are destroying my life, Martha.

1218
01:03:14,510 --> 01:03:16,190
Do you realize that's what you're doing?

1219
01:03:16,190 --> 01:03:18,100
I'll never forgive you, never.

1220
01:03:26,757 --> 01:03:31,757
(pool balls clattering)
(Linda gasps)

1221
01:03:34,770 --> 01:03:36,760
(ominous tones)

1222
01:03:36,760 --> 01:03:38,010
- Are you okay?

1223
01:03:38,959 --> 01:03:41,376
(Linda sobs)

1224
01:03:43,599 --> 01:03:45,932
Come on, I'll get us a beer.

1225
01:04:04,090 --> 01:04:05,410
- Thanks for coming.

1226
01:04:05,410 --> 01:04:07,750
I just didn't want to be alone.

1227
01:04:07,750 --> 01:04:08,900
- Your sister?
- Yeah.

1228
01:04:10,280 --> 01:04:11,320
- Come on.

1229
01:04:11,320 --> 01:04:12,350
I got some good news.

1230
01:04:12,350 --> 01:04:13,980
I've been doing some checking.

1231
01:04:13,980 --> 01:04:16,440
Archie Maddox did indeed
have a daughter named Tina.

1232
01:04:16,440 --> 01:04:20,983
Only the Hall of Records
claiming she died 10 years ago.

1233
01:04:21,860 --> 01:04:23,410
- But the kids said they
just saw her a year a go.

1234
01:04:23,410 --> 01:04:25,150
- Yeah, well, if that's true,

1235
01:04:25,150 --> 01:04:27,803
then obviously someone
fake the death certificate.

1236
01:04:34,040 --> 01:04:35,420
- Did Archie have any other relatives

1237
01:04:35,420 --> 01:04:36,790
who could have inherited his land?

1238
01:04:36,790 --> 01:04:38,290
- Nope, I checked.

1239
01:04:38,290 --> 01:04:40,930
And with Tina legally
dead, Potter was able

1240
01:04:40,930 --> 01:04:43,300
to buy Archie's land in a public auction

1241
01:04:43,300 --> 01:04:45,220
and he got it cheap.

1242
01:04:45,220 --> 01:04:46,053
- What about Tina?

1243
01:04:46,053 --> 01:04:48,870
- Well Mr. Potter's not gonna tell us.

1244
01:04:48,870 --> 01:04:50,150
- So I guess that means

1245
01:04:50,150 --> 01:04:52,554
we're on our way to see Hilda Potter.

1246
01:04:52,554 --> 01:04:53,387
- Mm hmm.

1247
01:05:04,350 --> 01:05:05,693
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

1248
01:05:24,189 --> 01:05:27,653
- I always add extra water,
it gets too sweet for me.

1249
01:05:31,710 --> 01:05:35,163
Whew, I can't bear this heat.

1250
01:05:39,270 --> 01:05:42,810
I can't imagine how you
think I can help you.

1251
01:05:42,810 --> 01:05:45,570
- Oh, you understand this is unofficial,

1252
01:05:45,570 --> 01:05:48,710
we're just trying to
tie up some loose hands.

1253
01:05:48,710 --> 01:05:51,860
- Well, I'm really not aware

1254
01:05:51,860 --> 01:05:53,780
of what goes on outside this house.

1255
01:05:53,780 --> 01:05:58,080
I uh, I, you know I do get out
of bit to see a few friends,

1256
01:05:58,080 --> 01:06:03,080
but my life is really my flowers.

1257
01:06:04,320 --> 01:06:05,763
These are from my nursery.

1258
01:06:07,030 --> 01:06:08,230
- Oh, they're beautiful.

1259
01:06:09,720 --> 01:06:11,483
- People say it's an ugly world.

1260
01:06:12,850 --> 01:06:15,533
Flowers remind me that
the blame lies elsewhere.

1261
01:06:21,450 --> 01:06:22,623
- Are those your sons?

1262
01:06:23,590 --> 01:06:24,423
- Yes.

1263
01:06:27,030 --> 01:06:29,890
- We understand that
you would occasionally

1264
01:06:29,890 --> 01:06:31,693
visit a young girl.

1265
01:06:33,000 --> 01:06:35,500
(door creaks)

1266
01:06:40,970 --> 01:06:41,990
- What are y'all doing here?

1267
01:06:41,990 --> 01:06:43,013
- Doyle, they just-

1268
01:06:45,740 --> 01:06:47,920
- You got no business here.

1269
01:06:47,920 --> 01:06:50,350
- Well, as I was telling your wife,

1270
01:06:50,350 --> 01:06:51,803
it's an unofficial visit.

1271
01:06:52,890 --> 01:06:56,243
- We've got a call first
policy in my house.

1272
01:06:57,390 --> 01:06:59,183
- Look, they didn't do any-

1273
01:07:02,200 --> 01:07:04,493
- Sorry for the intrusion Mrs. Potter.

1274
01:07:13,575 --> 01:07:16,082
That produced a whole lot of nothing.

1275
01:07:16,082 --> 01:07:17,082
- It produced a lie.

1276
01:07:18,360 --> 01:07:19,193
- What do you mean?

1277
01:07:19,193 --> 01:07:21,930
- Well at Linda's, Potter
said they only had one son.

1278
01:07:21,930 --> 01:07:23,930
She just admitted they have two.

1279
01:07:23,930 --> 01:07:26,270
There was a family picture with two sons

1280
01:07:26,270 --> 01:07:28,090
and then a class picture.

1281
01:07:28,090 --> 01:07:30,483
A school called Rosedale Hall.

1282
01:07:31,529 --> 01:07:33,581
- I've never heard of it,
but I'll check it out.

1283
01:07:33,581 --> 01:07:34,414
- Okay.

1284
01:07:35,610 --> 01:07:38,650
- We've got ourselves a real
potential problem here, Eddie

1285
01:07:38,650 --> 01:07:39,910
and you're the cause of it.

1286
01:07:39,910 --> 01:07:42,320
- Mr. Potter, I think I
got the situation in hand.

1287
01:07:42,320 --> 01:07:46,210
- You've got your life in
your hands is what you've got.

1288
01:07:46,210 --> 01:07:49,190
That bitch is gonna get
chatty to a grand jury.

1289
01:07:49,190 --> 01:07:50,280
- She ain't gonna say nothing.

1290
01:07:50,280 --> 01:07:52,510
I mean, she, she don't want-
