1291
01:07:52,510 --> 01:07:54,680
I've had some calls. I
know what she's gonna do.

1292
01:07:54,680 --> 01:07:55,980
Now, I've got an alibi.

1293
01:07:55,980 --> 01:07:56,900
And so have the boys.

1294
01:07:56,900 --> 01:07:58,720
We were playing cards together.

1295
01:07:58,720 --> 01:08:01,810
You're gonna take this
fall by yourself, Eddie.

1296
01:08:01,810 --> 01:08:03,210
- Yeah but you said, I mean,

1297
01:08:04,410 --> 01:08:06,890
I mean about friends
and sticking together.

1298
01:08:06,890 --> 01:08:08,640
- The bottom line, Eddie,

1299
01:08:08,640 --> 01:08:11,323
is we do what's right for Rocky Valley.

1300
01:08:12,230 --> 01:08:14,283
Now I'm bringing in jobs.

1301
01:08:15,860 --> 01:08:17,163
What are you bringing in?

1302
01:08:18,670 --> 01:08:21,143
Mr. Potter, me and Linda,
we owe you everything.

1303
01:08:22,000 --> 01:08:24,250
We wouldn't let anybody
cause you no trouble.

1304
01:08:28,290 --> 01:08:30,100
(Doyle laughs)

1305
01:08:30,100 --> 01:08:35,100
- Well, just keep that
sister-in-law of yours

1306
01:08:36,130 --> 01:08:38,143
from testifying, that's all, Eddie.

1307
01:08:42,700 --> 01:08:43,623
Goodbye, Eddie.

1308
01:08:59,770 --> 01:09:00,660
- Well she's gotta go.

1309
01:09:00,660 --> 01:09:01,780
You got to make her go

1310
01:09:01,780 --> 01:09:03,290
or they're gonna do something desperate.

1311
01:09:03,290 --> 01:09:04,650
- Eddie, why are you so upset?

1312
01:09:04,650 --> 01:09:05,790
Did somebody threaten you?

1313
01:09:05,790 --> 01:09:07,177
- I'm worried for you and the kids.

1314
01:09:07,177 --> 01:09:09,590
- Oh, they threatened us and
you're gonna defend them.

1315
01:09:09,590 --> 01:09:11,030
Who are they, Eddie?

1316
01:09:11,030 --> 01:09:13,710
- Honey, you know you are not
seeing the bigger picture.

1317
01:09:13,710 --> 01:09:15,327
Alright?

1318
01:09:15,327 --> 01:09:18,160
And your sister's ruining
everything for them, for us.

1319
01:09:18,160 --> 01:09:19,930
And we're the town too.

1320
01:09:19,930 --> 01:09:21,090
- No, they're the town.

1321
01:09:21,090 --> 01:09:22,540
You're the ex-con they helped.

1322
01:09:22,540 --> 01:09:24,083
And I'm the ex con's wife.

1323
01:09:26,510 --> 01:09:27,720
- They like us.

1324
01:09:27,720 --> 01:09:29,043
- As long as we're grateful.

1325
01:09:31,120 --> 01:09:33,225
We don't owe them anything.

1326
01:09:33,225 --> 01:09:36,495
- That's what Archie said,
look what happened to him.

1327
01:09:36,495 --> 01:09:39,765
(ominous tones)

1328
01:09:39,765 --> 01:09:42,682
- How do you know what Archie said?

1329
01:09:45,877 --> 01:09:47,437
You were there, weren't you?

1330
01:09:47,437 --> 01:09:48,837
- No, I wasn't there.

1331
01:09:48,837 --> 01:09:49,786
- What really happened, Eddie?

1332
01:09:49,786 --> 01:09:53,286
- I don't know. I told you I wasn't there.

1333
01:09:54,416 --> 01:09:55,523
- You were there. You know what happened.

1334
01:09:55,523 --> 01:09:57,883
And you've gotta tell me.

1335
01:09:59,576 --> 01:10:00,500
Eddie!

1336
01:10:00,500 --> 01:10:01,400
- All right. I was there.

1337
01:10:01,400 --> 01:10:02,803
All right? I was there.

1338
01:10:06,323 --> 01:10:07,910
But I was in the car.

1339
01:10:07,910 --> 01:10:09,460
I was driving for Mr. Potter

1340
01:10:09,460 --> 01:10:11,010
and I didn't get outta the car.

1341
01:10:13,640 --> 01:10:16,500
Old Archie got drunk,
knocked over a kerosene lamp.

1342
01:10:16,500 --> 01:10:18,110
You know the story, the
whole town knows the story

1343
01:10:18,110 --> 01:10:19,900
and it's the truth.

1344
01:10:19,900 --> 01:10:20,733
I swear it.

1345
01:10:21,810 --> 01:10:23,010
- And what about Larson?

1346
01:10:26,343 --> 01:10:27,843
Eddie, look at me.

1347
01:10:30,170 --> 01:10:31,003
Who shot Larson?

1348
01:10:31,003 --> 01:10:32,973
- I don't know. Now you leave me alone.

1349
01:10:39,564 --> 01:10:41,564
- It was you, wasn't it?

1350
01:10:46,013 --> 01:10:48,880
- It was supposed to be a warning.

1351
01:10:48,880 --> 01:10:49,730
I didn't mean it.

1352
01:10:53,135 --> 01:10:54,218
Listen to me.

1353
01:10:55,132 --> 01:10:57,263
I only wanted to scare him.

1354
01:10:57,263 --> 01:10:58,563
I didn't mean to hurt him.

1355
01:11:02,610 --> 01:11:05,042
Oh baby.

1356
01:11:05,042 --> 01:11:05,875
Oh.

1357
01:11:14,223 --> 01:11:15,056
- Eddie!

1358
01:11:17,697 --> 01:11:20,670
All your life, just
one mess after another.

1359
01:11:27,640 --> 01:11:30,123
- Thanks.

1360
01:11:34,922 --> 01:11:37,420
- You know I grew up in
a town like Rocky Valley.

1361
01:11:37,420 --> 01:11:38,970
Life like this.

1362
01:11:38,970 --> 01:11:40,450
I hated it.

1363
01:11:40,450 --> 01:11:41,913
- I like small towns.

1364
01:11:48,120 --> 01:11:48,953
I bet you don't even know

1365
01:11:48,953 --> 01:11:51,440
the name of your neighbor in the city.

1366
01:11:51,440 --> 01:11:52,670
- Yes I do.

1367
01:11:52,670 --> 01:11:54,002
Her name is 417.

1368
01:11:54,002 --> 01:11:57,510
- (laughs) Yeah, I know
you're being funny,

1369
01:11:57,510 --> 01:12:01,560
but I think you like it that way.

1370
01:12:01,560 --> 01:12:04,210
- I like knowing who I am
and making peace with that.

1371
01:12:05,380 --> 01:12:06,700
- That makes you happy?

1372
01:12:06,700 --> 01:12:07,733
- Makes me content.

1373
01:12:08,900 --> 01:12:10,300
- What would make you happy?

1374
01:12:12,720 --> 01:12:15,646
- To not be depressed by
the downside of my choices.

1375
01:12:15,646 --> 01:12:18,229
(Akins laughs)

1376
01:12:20,470 --> 01:12:22,820
- I gather you've decided
not to have a family.

1377
01:12:24,110 --> 01:12:25,860
- Apparently the same goes for you.

1378
01:12:27,466 --> 01:12:29,320
(sad music)

1379
01:12:29,320 --> 01:12:34,220
- My wife and boy were
killed by a drunk driver.

1380
01:12:34,220 --> 01:12:35,733
- Oh Brooke, I'm so sorry.

1381
01:12:36,956 --> 01:12:39,706
- I'm still not afraid to
start another family, though.

1382
01:12:41,168 --> 01:12:43,118
- You have a lot more guts than I have.

1383
01:12:44,180 --> 01:12:47,590
Success in life to me is
how well I handle plan B.

1384
01:12:47,590 --> 01:12:49,640
- So you're happier with the compromises?

1385
01:12:51,820 --> 01:12:54,616
- Only because the
unhappiest people I know

1386
01:12:54,616 --> 01:12:57,500
are the ones who are surprised
that life isn't fair.

1387
01:12:57,500 --> 01:12:58,763
I don't like surprises.

1388
01:13:01,709 --> 01:13:06,440
- Well, Ms. Martha, I like you.

1389
01:13:06,440 --> 01:13:07,313
Surprised?

1390
01:13:18,787 --> 01:13:20,147
- [Linda] Goodnight, Brooke.

1391
01:13:20,147 --> 01:13:21,897
- [Brooke] Goodnight.

1392
01:13:28,554 --> 01:13:33,554
(soft music)
(patrons conversing quietly)

1393
01:13:55,233 --> 01:13:57,400
- [Man] Get on outta here.

1394
01:14:00,313 --> 01:14:04,455
(man clears his throat)

1395
01:14:04,455 --> 01:14:05,788
- [Man] Bye bye.

1396
01:14:07,551 --> 01:14:09,149
- [Man] We better go back in.

1397
01:14:09,149 --> 01:14:10,949
My brother.
- Oh yeah.

1398
01:14:10,949 --> 01:14:12,282
- [Man] Alright.

1399
01:14:13,829 --> 01:14:15,579
(engine revs)

1400
01:14:15,579 --> 01:14:16,780
(tense music)

1401
01:14:16,780 --> 01:14:19,363
(Martha pants)

1402
01:14:36,030 --> 01:14:38,280
(crashing)

1403
01:14:40,477 --> 01:14:43,310
(Martha exclaims)

1404
01:14:55,845 --> 01:14:58,797
- (groans) I'm okay. Really, I'm fine.

1405
01:15:01,240 --> 01:15:03,300
- (sighs) Well what you described

1406
01:15:03,300 --> 01:15:04,900
is a four wheeler with light bars.

1407
01:15:04,900 --> 01:15:08,445
2/3 of the vehicles in this
town are four wheelers.

1408
01:15:08,445 --> 01:15:10,760
- Yeah, but this one had
a piece of a barn on it.

1409
01:15:10,760 --> 01:15:13,260
- Now will you allow me
to assign you a deputy?

1410
01:15:13,260 --> 01:15:14,093
- A local?

1411
01:15:14,093 --> 01:15:16,627
- No, I can get someone
from another jurisdiction.

1412
01:15:16,627 --> 01:15:17,623
- That'd take a lotta time.

1413
01:15:17,623 --> 01:15:19,203
Well, I'll get right on it.

1414
01:15:20,534 --> 01:15:23,523
And I'll get someone to
pick up your car too.

1415
01:15:26,297 --> 01:15:28,401
- Thanks, Brooke.
- Sure.

1416
01:15:28,401 --> 01:15:29,401
- Goodnight.

1417
01:16:23,094 --> 01:16:25,135
- [Woman] Come on. Now
you're getting the towel wet.

1418
01:16:25,135 --> 01:16:26,434
- [Girl] A little splash.

1419
01:16:26,434 --> 01:16:27,827
- [Woman] Oh good. Well come on.

1420
01:16:27,827 --> 01:16:28,967
- [Man] The suntan lotion.

1421
01:16:28,967 --> 01:16:30,203
- [Woman] There you go.

1422
01:16:32,728 --> 01:16:34,328
- I'm sorry about what happened.

1423
01:16:37,320 --> 01:16:38,153
I'm sorry.

1424
01:16:42,202 --> 01:16:43,553
Is there somewhere we can talk?

1425
01:16:46,818 --> 01:16:50,133
- [Man] Y'all stay where I can see ya.

1426
01:16:50,133 --> 01:16:54,133
- [Woman] That's good
honey, all the way across.

1427
01:17:07,300 --> 01:17:09,073
- Sounds like dad's old Plymouth.

1428
01:17:11,798 --> 01:17:12,631
(Linda sighs)

1429
01:17:12,631 --> 01:17:17,053
- It, it's just, I know everything now.

1430
01:17:18,410 --> 01:17:19,960
- I know that Eddie was there

1431
01:17:19,960 --> 01:17:23,423
when Archie Maddox died, and
I know Eddie shot Larson.

1432
01:17:25,620 --> 01:17:26,453
- Oh thank God.

1433
01:17:29,400 --> 01:17:31,667
Now you see why you and the
kids have to come away with me.

1434
01:17:31,667 --> 01:17:33,813
No, but Eddie told me what happened

1435
01:17:33,813 --> 01:17:35,490
and I know what he did is wrong.

1436
01:17:35,490 --> 01:17:36,770
- Don't finish that sentence, Linda.

1437
01:17:36,770 --> 01:17:38,330
- He's my husband, Martha, and

1438
01:17:38,330 --> 01:17:40,560
- How can I shake some sense into you?

1439
01:17:40,560 --> 01:17:41,680
Don't you see the pattern?

1440
01:17:41,680 --> 01:17:43,210
Mother never listened either.

1441
01:17:43,210 --> 01:17:44,790
Her death was an escape.

1442
01:17:44,790 --> 01:17:47,920
It was easier for her to
die than to face reality.

1443
01:17:47,920 --> 01:17:50,780
(tense music)

1444
01:17:50,780 --> 01:17:53,240
Linda, wait, please listen to me.

1445
01:17:53,240 --> 01:17:55,770
- You don't give people
any room do ya, Martha?

1446
01:17:55,770 --> 01:17:57,570
And if they take too much
time finding themselves,

1447
01:17:57,570 --> 01:17:58,810
you just dump 'em.

1448
01:17:58,810 --> 01:18:00,520
Eddie's right, you don't care about me.

1449
01:18:00,520 --> 01:18:01,410
- That's not true.

1450
01:18:01,410 --> 01:18:03,160
- You're selfish, Martha, you always were.

1451
01:18:03,160 --> 01:18:05,480
That's why you bailed out on me.

1452
01:18:05,480 --> 01:18:07,210
- I know the responsibility
I left you with.

1453
01:18:07,210 --> 01:18:08,590
I felt guilty my whole life.

1454
01:18:08,590 --> 01:18:09,860
- Oh, I'll make ya a deal.

1455
01:18:09,860 --> 01:18:12,630
I'll take your guilt if you
give me those years back.

1456
01:18:12,630 --> 01:18:14,310
I figure you owe me one, Martha.

1457
01:18:14,310 --> 01:18:15,143
- I do owe you.

1458
01:18:15,143 --> 01:18:16,380
- You want to help me and the kids?

1459
01:18:16,380 --> 01:18:17,700
You want to make things right?

1460
01:18:17,700 --> 01:18:18,533
- Yes.

1461
01:18:18,533 --> 01:18:19,780
- Then lie to the grand jury

1462
01:18:19,780 --> 01:18:21,380
and don't tell them about Eddie.

1463
01:18:22,715 --> 01:18:25,290
(explosion booms)
(women exclaim)

1464
01:18:25,290 --> 01:18:27,873
(Linda grunts)

1465
01:18:32,570 --> 01:18:34,170
- Oh, not necessary.

1466
01:18:34,170 --> 01:18:35,070
- Come on, get in.

1467
01:18:35,070 --> 01:18:36,113
It's hospital rules.

1468
01:18:37,651 --> 01:18:38,901
Thank you, I'll take her.

1469
01:18:43,112 --> 01:18:44,210
Your sister okay?

1470
01:18:44,210 --> 01:18:45,043
- Yeah.

1471
01:18:46,310 --> 01:18:47,460
- I'll put you up in my hotel.

1472
01:18:47,460 --> 01:18:48,760
They won't touch ya there.

1473
01:18:49,727 --> 01:18:51,684
You alright? You cold?

1474
01:18:51,684 --> 01:18:52,517
- Yeah.

1475
01:18:52,517 --> 01:18:54,203
I guess it's a delayed
reaction or something.

1476
01:18:55,700 --> 01:18:56,960
Thanks.
- There you go.

1477
01:18:56,960 --> 01:18:58,290
- Could we stop by Linda's

1478
01:18:58,290 --> 01:18:59,872
so I can get something else to wear?

1479
01:18:59,872 --> 01:19:01,539
- Yeah, sure.
- Okay.

1480
01:19:02,930 --> 01:19:04,480
- I have some interesting news.

1481
01:19:05,800 --> 01:19:09,090
That school photograph you
saw at the Potter's house.

1482
01:19:09,090 --> 01:19:11,290
- Rosedale Hall?
- Yeah. It's in Galveston.

1483
01:19:12,290 --> 01:19:14,000
It's a special school.

1484
01:19:14,000 --> 01:19:15,150
- [Martha] Special how?

1485
01:19:16,520 --> 01:19:18,053
- For impaired children.

1486
01:19:21,930 --> 01:19:22,780
I'll get the car.

1487
01:19:25,040 --> 01:19:25,873
Mrs. Potter.

1488
01:19:27,680 --> 01:19:29,080
- Are you all right?

1489
01:19:29,080 --> 01:19:29,913
- I'm fine.

1490
01:19:30,951 --> 01:19:32,843
- How is your sister?
I came to check on her.

1491
01:19:32,843 --> 01:19:34,870
- Well she's going to be okay.

1492
01:19:34,870 --> 01:19:37,423
Mrs. Potter, could I talk to you?

1493
01:19:38,690 --> 01:19:39,523
- I can't.

1494
01:19:41,210 --> 01:19:45,890
- Mrs. Potter, your husband
said that you have only one son.

1495
01:19:45,890 --> 01:19:49,760
At your house there were two
boys in the photo next to you.

1496
01:19:49,760 --> 01:19:51,320
Why did you lie?

1497
01:19:51,320 --> 01:19:53,900
- I had two sons.

1498
01:19:53,900 --> 01:19:54,883
One is dead.

1499
01:19:55,880 --> 01:19:57,160
The other is fine.

1500
01:19:57,160 --> 01:19:59,320
In spite of what his father says.

1501
01:19:59,320 --> 01:20:01,120
- May I ask how your other son died?

1502
01:20:02,120 --> 01:20:04,253
- No.
- Mrs. Potter.

1503
01:20:05,330 --> 01:20:06,433
I know about Tina.

1504
01:20:07,890 --> 01:20:10,810
I know she's Archie's
daughter and used to bring her

1505
01:20:10,810 --> 01:20:12,150
to visit him.

1506
01:20:12,150 --> 01:20:13,600
Now the secrets that are buried here

1507
01:20:13,600 --> 01:20:16,140
are gonna come out with or without you.

1508
01:20:16,140 --> 01:20:17,940
You're gonna have to face that fact.

1509
01:20:24,740 --> 01:20:26,390
- You're doing real well, Brenda.

1510
01:20:27,577 --> 01:20:29,536
Keep going now.

1511
01:20:29,536 --> 01:20:30,682
Yeah.

1512
01:20:30,682 --> 01:20:31,743
There.

1513
01:20:31,743 --> 01:20:33,326
There you go. Good.

1514
01:20:36,278 --> 01:20:38,493
That a girl, Brenda.

1515
01:20:38,493 --> 01:20:40,740
- This the same school
you saw in the picture?

1516
01:20:40,740 --> 01:20:41,990
- Well, it looks like it.

1517
01:20:45,601 --> 01:20:47,951
- [Woman] We could just go down the block.

1518
01:20:47,951 --> 01:20:49,451
- Alright.
- Down the corner.

1519
01:20:50,350 --> 01:20:52,780
- [Woman] Ready for our field
to look so much better now.

1520
01:20:52,780 --> 01:20:54,390
- Well, I think it was the flowers here

1521
01:20:54,390 --> 01:20:55,580
that convinced Hilda Potter

1522
01:20:55,580 --> 01:20:57,780
this should be the home for her son.

1523
01:20:57,780 --> 01:20:59,320
- How'd he die?

1524
01:20:59,320 --> 01:21:03,590
- Uremia, poor little guy,
one thing after another.

1525
01:21:03,590 --> 01:21:05,044
- Well, what was the matter with him?

1526
01:21:05,044 --> 01:21:07,240
- Galactosemia.
- What's that?

1527
01:21:07,240 --> 01:21:09,920
Disturbance in the
metabolism of milk, sugar,

1528
01:21:09,920 --> 01:21:12,030
retardation, underdeveloped physically,

1529
01:21:12,030 --> 01:21:13,280
large liver and spleen.

1530
01:21:13,280 --> 01:21:14,510
- Brooke?

1531
01:21:14,510 --> 01:21:17,400
The kids said that there was
something strange about Tina.

1532
01:21:17,400 --> 01:21:18,570
They could've meant retarded.

1533
01:21:18,570 --> 01:21:20,142
- [Nurse] That's odd.

1534
01:21:20,142 --> 01:21:20,975
- What?

1535
01:21:21,870 --> 01:21:23,570
- Mrs. Potter comes to visit a young girl

1536
01:21:23,570 --> 01:21:25,560
that she and Mr. Potter
brought us about a year ago

1537
01:21:25,560 --> 01:21:27,250
from an institution.

1538
01:21:27,250 --> 01:21:30,423
Her name is Katie Bass,
but she calls herself Tina.

1539
01:21:34,540 --> 01:21:37,113
A lotta these paintings
on the wall are Katie's.

1540
01:21:38,080 --> 01:21:41,997
(residents chattering quietly)

1541
01:21:51,915 --> 01:21:53,020
Hi, Katie.

1542
01:21:53,020 --> 01:21:54,750
Someone wants to talk to you, sweetie.

1543
01:21:54,750 --> 01:21:55,583
- Hi.

1544
01:21:56,879 --> 01:21:57,712
- Hi.

1545
01:21:58,670 --> 01:21:59,720
- Did you paint this?

1546
01:22:00,590 --> 01:22:01,550
- Yeah.

1547
01:22:01,550 --> 01:22:04,410
- Oh it's a sunset. It's just beautiful.

1548
01:22:04,410 --> 01:22:05,243
- Thanks.

1549
01:22:07,160 --> 01:22:09,033
- You have her records?
- Of course.

1550
01:22:10,810 --> 01:22:11,960
- I'll bet they're forged.

1551
01:22:11,960 --> 01:22:13,100
- I beg your pardon.

1552
01:22:13,100 --> 01:22:14,520
- We have reason to believe

1553
01:22:14,520 --> 01:22:18,750
Katie Bass' real name is Tina Maddox.

1554
01:22:18,750 --> 01:22:21,463
- But the Potters themselves
brought her to us.

1555
01:22:24,040 --> 01:22:25,851
- Did you paint this for me?

1556
01:22:25,851 --> 01:22:26,909
- Yeah.

1557
01:22:26,909 --> 01:22:29,163
- Oh, thank you, Tina.

1558
01:22:30,820 --> 01:22:31,653
- Tina.

1559
01:22:38,098 --> 01:22:40,765
(ominous tones)

1560
01:23:01,404 --> 01:23:02,904
- [Eddie] Come on.

1561
01:23:14,956 --> 01:23:16,289
What's going on?

1562
01:23:18,710 --> 01:23:21,783
- Eddie, we need to talk.

1563
01:23:22,893 --> 01:23:24,584
- You kids go on, get in the house.

1564
01:23:24,584 --> 01:23:27,167
Come on, get in there. Come on.

1565
01:23:34,403 --> 01:23:37,500
- Eddie, I think I figured
a way outta this mess

1566
01:23:37,500 --> 01:23:38,333
you got us into.

1567
01:23:40,396 --> 01:23:42,813
- Mr. Potter, me and Linda...

1568
01:23:54,389 --> 01:23:57,056
(Eddie panting)

1569
01:24:08,269 --> 01:24:09,102
- Eddie?

1570
01:24:10,331 --> 01:24:11,164
Eddie?

1571
01:24:12,118 --> 01:24:13,929
